{"name": "conversationalspacemapapp", "metadata": {"name": "ConversationalSpaceMapApp", "version": "0.0.4", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.13"], "home_page": null, "license": "BSD-3-Clause License", "documentation_url": "https://github.com/manuelbieri/ConversationalSpaceMap", "dependencies": ["toga-chart", "toga", "mockito"], "summary": "Generate conversational space maps for interview data.", "upload_time": 1734207986}, "documentation": ["# Conversational Space Map App\n\nGenerate conversational space maps for interview data, inspired by Saunders et al. (2023, pp. 458-460).\n\n```{image} https://raw.githubusercontent.com/manuelbieri/ConversationalSpaceMapApp/master/src/conversationalspacemapapp/resources/Screenshot.png\n:align: center\n:alt: App screenshot\n:width: 600\n```\n\n## Quickstart\n\nNote: This quickstart guide assumes that you have already installed Python and Git.\n\n1. Download or clone the repository\n\n```bash\n$ git clone https://github.com/manuelbieri/ConversationalSpaceMap.git\n```\n\n2. Create a virtual environment.\n3. Install dependencies (in your virtual environment).\n\n```bash\n$ pip install .\n```\n\n4. Run the app ([see this tutorial](https://docs.beeware.org/en/latest/tutorial/tutorial-3.html#building-your-application)).\n\n```bash\n$ briefcase run\n```\n\n(5. Package the app for local installation)\n\n```bash\n$ briefcase package\n```\n\n## How to use\n\n```{image} https://raw.githubusercontent.com/manuelbieri/ConversationalSpaceMapApp/master/src/conversationalspacemapapp/resources/Menubar.png\n:align: center\n:alt: Menubar screenshot\n:width: 600\n```\n\n## References\n\n**Saunders, Mark, Philip Lewis, and Adrian Thornhill**, *Research methods for business students*, 9 ed., Harlow, England: Pearson, 2023.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "conversationalspacemapapp", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "vari